Types
=====

TypeT.scala: basic types

TypeConstraint.scala: constraints on types (includes TypeEnv0).

FunctionType.scala: types of functions.

EvaluationTypeEnv.scala: a type environment used during evaluation.

Values
======

Input.scala: input to the parser, either from the script or a cell.  Also includes the type ParseRsult.

Value.scala: values of expressions.

BuiltInFunctions.scala: definitions of the built-in functions.

Syntax
======

HasExtent.scala: trait giving the string from which the result of a parse is
produced.

Exp.scala: abstract syntax for expressions in the script.

Statement.scala: abstract syntax for statements in the script.

Parsing
=======

Parser.scala: general parsing combinators.

Parser0.scala: base class of various parsers.  Includes TypeParser, parser for
types.

ExpParser.scala: Parsing of expressions.

DeclarationParser.scala: parsing of declarations. REMOVED

StatementParser.scala: parsing of statements. 

CellParser.scala: CellParser and CSVParser, parsers for cells and CSV files,
respectively.

ExpParserTest.scala: test of parsing expressions.
 
StatementParserTest.scala: test of parsing statements

ParserTest.scala: test of parser.

Type checking
=============

Reply.scala: the result of a typecheck (Ok or Failure).  

Substitution.scala: substitution in types.

TypeEnv.scala: a type environment for type checking.

TypeParamSubstitution.scala: substitution of type parameters by type
variables, and back again.

Unification.scala: unification of types. 

TypeChecker0.scala: some basics for the type checker, including
ExpTypeCheckerT (interface of ExpTypeChecker to sub-typecheckers),
BinOpTypeChecker (type checking of binary operations), and CellReadTypeChecker
(type checking of cell reads).

FunctionAppTypeChecker.scala: type checking of function applications.

ExpTypeChecker: type checker for expressions.

DeclarationTypeChecker.scala: type checker for declarations. REMOVED

TypeChecker.scala: the type checker.

TypeCheckerTest.scala: tests.

TypeCheckerTest0.scala: basic testing framework functions, and
TypeCheckTestExpr (for expressions).

TypeCheckerTest1.scala: basic tests on scripts: declarations, cell reads and
writes, lists.

TypeCheckerTest2.scala: tests on polymorphism, higher-order functions.

TypeCheckerTest3.scala: tests on for loops, overloading, and currying. 

TypeCheckerTest4.scala: tests on a Haskell-style prelude.

TypeCheckerTest5.scala: tests on tuples, calls, IF statements, operations.

Evaluation and execution
========================

CellWriteSource: The source for values produced by a cell write.  Also
contains MultipleWriteError.

EvaluationTypeChecker.scala -- why do we need this???  Checking a cell has
expected type, I think.

Environment.scala: environment used during evaluation. 

BinOpApply.scala: evaluation of binary operators. 

Execution.scala: main execution engine. 

EvaluationTest.scala: tests on the execution engine. 

Model
=====

ViewT.scala: The View, as seen by the model.

Model.scala: the model. 

TopLevelTest.scala: tests on the Model.

View
====

Spreadsheet.scala: the panel displaying the spreadsheet.

View.scala: the view.

Top level
=========

SpreadsheetApp.scala: the main application.

AllTests.scala: run all the tests. 